messages.message: In addition to the File System API, Notebooks are started by default with a  utility module called ‘ib’ (imported with i*mport instabase.notebook.ipython.utils as ib*)  which will provide basic file system functions see the ib.list_dir(…) example below:

Look up the following file in github, it will show what’s loaded on startup: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/apps/user-notebook/standalone-n[…]ok/src/py/instabase/notebook/profile_default/startup/startup.py (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/apps/user-notebook/standalone-notebook/src/py/instabase/notebook/profile_default/startup/startup.py)
